ith2">86. <span class="element-citation">Smith RE, Zweerink HJ, Joklik WK. Polypeptide components of virions, top component and cores of reovirus type 3. <span><span class="ref-journal">Virology. </span>1969;<span class="ref-vol">39</span>:791\xe2\x80\x93810.</span> [<a href="/pubmed/4311639" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2895667&amp;issue-id=188258&amp;journal-id=349&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=Virology&amp;title=Polypeptide+components+of+virions,+top+component+and+cores+of+reovirus+type+3.&amp;author=RE+Smith&amp;author=HJ+Zweerink&amp;author=WK+Joklik&amp;volume=39&amp;publication_year=1969&amp;pages=791-810&amp;pmid=4311639&amp;" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=other&amp;article-id=2895667&amp;issue-id=188258&amp;journal-id=349&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Content%20Provider%7CLink%7CGoogle%20Scholar">Google Scholar</a>]</span></span></div><div class="ref-cit-blk half_rhythm" id="ppat.1000980-Wetzel1">87. <span class="element-citation">Wetzel JD, Chappell JD, Fogo AB, Dermody TS. Efficiency of viral entry determines the capacity of murine erythroleukemia cells to support persistent infections by mammalian reoviruses. <span><span class="ref-journal">J Virol. </span>1997;<span class="ref-vol">71</span>:299\xe2\x80\x93306.</span> <span class="nowrap">[<a class="int-reflink" href="/pmc/articles/PMC191051/">PMC free article</a>]</span> [<a href="/pubmed/8985350" target="pmc_ext" ref="reftype=pubmed&amp;article-id=2895667&amp;issue-id=188258&amp;journal-id=349&amp;FROM=Article%7CCitationRef&amp;TO=Entrez%7CPubMed%7CRecord">PubMed</a>] <span class="nowrap">[<a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?journal=J+Virol&amp;title=Efficiency+of+viral+entry+determines+the+capacity+of+murine+erythroleukemia+cells+to+support+persistent+infections+by+mammalian+reoviruses.&amp;author=JD+Wetzel&amp;author=JD+Chappell&